# type: textblock
#: ../../doc/po4a.7.pod:31
msgid ""
"Addendums must be provided to the system as a file, with the first line "
"indicating where in the produced document they should be placed in a so "
"called Po4a header. The rest of the addendum file with be added verbatim in "
"the resulting document."
msgstr ""

# type: textblock
#: ../../doc/po4a.7.pod:36
msgid ""
"The header have a pretty rigid syntax: They must begin with \"PO4A-HEADER:"
"\", followed by a colon (;) separated list of fields, each of them having "
"the \"key=value\" syntax. Whitespaces ARE important. Note that you cannot "
"use the colon char (;) in the value, and that quoting it doesn't help. The "
"recognized keys are:"
